          <p id="ICFTU.IO.63">
      The ITUC was established in November 2006 by the merger of the International Confederation of Free Trade Unions (ICFTU, founded in 1949 by trade union federations that had withdrawn from the 
      <xr pageref="N" ref="WFTU.IO">World Federation of Trade Unions</xr>
      ), the World Confederation of Labour (founded in 1920 as the International Federation of Christian Trade Unions and reconstituted in 1968), and eight national trade union organizations. The ITUC aims to defend and promote the rights of working people. It encourages co-operation between trade unions, and campaigns for global coherence in developing policies that place investment in jobs, fair wages and social protection at the core of economic growth and social justice. The ITUC promotes participation by unions in policymaking.
    </p>
          <int-org-section id="ICFTU.IO.118" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Members</heading>
               <p id="ICFTU.IO.64">There are 340 affiliated member organizations in 169 countries and territories representing 191m. workers.</p>
