          <int-org-section id="ICFTU.IO.104" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>World Congress</heading>
               <p id="ICFTU.IO.65">The World Congress, the highest authority of the ITUC, meets in ordinary session at least once every four years. The fifth Congress was held in Melbourne, Australia, in November 2022. An extraordinary World Congress was convened in October 2023 (see under General Council).</p>
               <p id="ICFTU.IO.66">Delegations from national federations vary in size on the basis of their paying membership. The Congress examines past activities and financial reports of the Confederation; reports on the activities of the ITUC's regional organizations and on the Council of Global Unions (in which the ITUC participates); addresses general policy questions; maps out future plans; considers proposals for amendments to the Constitution and other proposals submitted by member organizations; and elects the General Council, the General Secretary and the Confederation's three auditors.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="IO-ITUC.001" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>General Council</heading>
               <p id="IO-ITUC.002">
        Elected by the Congress, the General Council comprises 70 members who represent regions (Europe: 26; the Americas: 18; Asia-Pacific: 15; Africa: 11), with a target of 40% minimum representation by women; six `at large members’ members nominated by the Council’s Women's Committee; and two `at large’ members nominated by its Youth Committee. The General Secretary of the 
        <xr pageref="N" ref="IO-ITUC.125">Pan-European Regional Council</xr>
        , Executive Secretary of the 
        <xr pageref="N" ref="ITUC.IO.ATUC.1">Arab Trade Union Confederation</xr>
        , and representatives of the Global Unions and of the Trade Union Advisory Committee to the 
        <xr pageref="N" ref="OECD.IO">Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development</xr>
         may also participate. The Council meets at least once a year and acts as the supreme authority of the Confederation between World Congresses, with responsibility for directing the activities of the Confederation and effecting decisions and recommendations of the Congress. The Council's agenda is prepared by the General Secretary. On 21 December 2022 an extraordinary meeting of the General Council suspended the organization’s recently elected General Secretary, Luca Visentini, who had been arrested in Belgium earlier in that month and questioned over his acceptance in October of a cash donation allegedly linked to sources in Qatar and Morocco. (Visentini denied any impropriety, claiming that no conditions had been attached to the gift.) In mid-January 2023 the Council established a Special Commission that was tasked with investigating the allegations against Visentini, and with conducting an external audit of the organization’s financial affairs and of its internal financial and electoral rules and procedures. An extraordinary meeting of the General Council convened on 11 March unanimously adopted the report presented by the Special Commission, which found no evidence that donations originating in Qatar or Morocco had influenced the ITUC’s policymaking or programming. The Council concluded, however, that it no longer had confidence in Luca Visentini’s tenure of the post of General Secretary. A new General Secretary, Luc Triangle, was elected at an extraordinary ITUC World Congress that was held in mid-October (having assumed the position initially in an acting capacity in May). The October Congress also adopted amendments to ITUC’s Constitution aimed at strengthening electoral procedures. Meanwhile, upon the recommendation of the Special Commission, the General Council determined to construct an explicit anti-corruption policy and code of conduct.
      </p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="ICFTU.IO.105" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Executive Bureau</heading>
               <p id="ICFTU.IO.67">At its first meeting after the regular World Congress the General Council elects an Executive Bureau, comprising the President, the General Secretary and up to 25 members of the General Council. The Executive Bureau is authorized to address questions of urgency that arise between meetings of the General Council, or which are entrusted to it by the General Council. The Bureau meets at least twice a year. The President is supported by two Deputy Presidents.</p>
